      <h2>茶的起源</h2>
      <p>茶树（Camellia sinensis）原产于中国西南与缅甸北部交界地区。传说在公元前2737年，神农氏在煮水时，几片茶叶飘入水中，发现其清香与提神效果，从此茶逐渐进入人们生活。[43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_tea?citationMarker=43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054&citationId=1 "Wikipedia")</p>

      <h2>茶的历史发展</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>公元前二千年：</strong>云南地区开始以茶入药。[43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_tea?citationMarker=43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054&citationId=1 "Wikipedia")</li>
        <li><strong>公元3世纪：</strong>中国医师华佗在医学著作中记载茶饮。[43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tea?citationMarker=43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054&citationId=2 "Wikipedia")</li>
        <li><strong>唐代：</strong>茶成为日常饮品，陆羽撰写《茶经》。[43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054](https://www.britannica.com/topic/tea-beverage?citationMarker=43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054&citationId=3 "Britannica")</li>
        <li><strong>16世纪：</strong>葡萄牙商人将茶引入欧洲。[43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tea?citationMarker=43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054&citationId=2 "Wikipedia")</li>
        <li><strong>17世纪：</strong>英国流行饮茶，并在印度、斯里兰卡推广种植。[43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054](https://www.britannica.com/topic/tea-beverage?citationMarker=43dcd9a7-70db-4a1f-b0ae-981daa162054&citationId=3 "Britannica")</li>
      </ul>
